Reference:
  Body: |
    In the Vedanta there are four Mahâvâkyas, so called： 1. 'Thou art
    That.' 2. i am Brahman.' 3. 'This Self is Brahman.' 4. 'Prajnâna
    (Absolute Knowledge) is Brahman.'
  Source:
    By: Sri Ramana Maharshi
    Title: Talks
    Location:
      Page: 223
---
That which is the finest essence -- this whole world has that as its Self. That
is Reality. That is Âtman. That art thou, Svetaketu.
